          "html_url": "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/commit/c8ac73be9368c9994b895d7ad6d94b446c943995"
        }
      ],
      "message": "init: Reserve file descriptors for IPC connections\n\nWhen -ipcbind is used, the node opens one listening socket FD per\nbound address and accepts concurrent IPC connections. Neither was\npreviously accounted for in min_required_fds, meaning IPC-heavy\nworkloads could silently exhaust available file descriptors at\nunpredictable moments.\n\nAdd -unixmaxconnections (default: 16, mirroring -rpcworkqueue) so\noperators can control how many FDs are reserved for accepted IPC\nconnections. Add ipc_bind to account for the listening socket FDs\nopened per -ipcbind address, which were previously unaccounted for.\nEmit a warning when -unixmaxconnections is set without -ipcbind. Log\nthe total IPC FD reservation at startup so operators can verify it.\n\nSuggested by Sjors in #32297 (comment).",
      "committer": {
        "name": "Enoch Azariah",
        "email": "enirox001@gmail.com",
        "date": "2026-04-01T13:26:58Z"
      },
      "author": {
        "name": "Enoch Azariah",
        "email": "enirox001@gmail.com",
        "date": "2026-04-01T12:48:40Z"
      },
      "sha": "00d28987a3cd996c41bdfc8c93e6d9563f1df498"
    },
