      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "> I think it should, because the error for running out file descriptors is presumably confusing, and it will happen at unpredictable moments depending on how many RPC, P2P and IPC connections are active.\r\n\r\nRegarding the hard connection limit at the accept loop, implementing that would require changes to mp::ListenConnections in libmultiprocess. Would you expect that to be done in this PR, or as a follow-up in libmultiprocess?",
